  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;The development hereby permitted shall only be carried out and completed strictly in accordance with the submitted plans hereby approved and any subsequent approval of details.\r\n&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;\r\nREASON: To ensure that the development hereby permitted is carried out in full accordance with the plans hereby approved.\r\n&lt;/p&gt;",
    "<p>The development hereby permitted must be begun not later than the expiration of three years beginning with the date of this permission.</p><p><br></p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\nREASON: In order to comply with the provisions of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).</p><p>\r\n</p>",
    "&lt;p&gt;All replacement windows and doors relating to this flats conversion scheme shall be timber framed and not aluminium/metal to be in keeping with the materiality of the existing building as shown on revised materials specification drawing 058_TR_801 Rev A.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;REASON:&amp;nbsp; In the interests of visual amenity and to protect the character and appearance of the De Beauvoir Conservation Area.&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p class=&quot;MsoNormal&quot; style=&quot;margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family:&amp;quot;PT Sans&amp;quot;,sans-serif;mso-fareast-font-family:&amp;quot;Times New Roman&amp;quot;;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:Arial;color:#222222;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:\r\nnone;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB&quot;&gt;The noise level from the Air Source Heat Pump\r\n(ASHP) included in the approved development shall at all times remain 10dB(A)\r\nbelow background levels when measured at any nearby residential window.&lt;br&gt;\r\n&lt;br&gt;\r\nREASON: To ensure that occupiers of neighbouring properties do not suffer a\r\nloss of residential amenity by reason of noise nuisance and other excess noise.&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;A scheme for the provision and implementation of flood resilient and resistant construction details and measures for the development against surface water flood risk, such as the incorporation of linear slot drains, shall be submitted to and agreed in writing with the LPA in consultation with the LLFA prior to the construction of the measures.&amp;nbsp; The scheme shall be carried out in its entirety before the development is occupied and constructed and completed in accordance with the approved plans in line with current best practices.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;REASON: To ensure that the development will provide a sustainable drainage system.&amp;nbsp; The condition is required to be discharged prior to the commencement of development to ensure that sustainable drainage is incorporated into the design of the development.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Pre-commencement condition justification:&amp;nbsp; To ensure that the development is protected against surface water flood risk.&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
